  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6524.35 sitting just below the GEX flip at 6532 in a BREAKOUT regime, dealers are currently short gamma and likely selling into this move as spot approaches the massive +3165.9M positive gamma wall at 6525. The recent wall break and GEX surge indicate dealers just got squeezed out of hedges, creating amplified momentum that should continue until we either breach 6532 (flip to supportive regime) or get rejected hard at the 6525 resistance wall. Watch 6515 closely - any dip back to that -4364.7M negative gamma level will trigger aggressive dealer buying that could rocket price back toward the flip, while a clean break above 6532 puts dealers in buy-the-dip mode with upside targets at 6550.",
